Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Peel the @potatoes{1}(peeled and sliced into thin rounds approximately 1cm thick). When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until just tender, ~{14-16%mins}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through, but be careful not to overcook them.

Once cooked, carefully drain in a #colander{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}(thinly sliced). Trim the @carrots{2}(trimmed and halved lengthways, no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Pop the carrots onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1}(for roasting), season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer, then set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press). Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and @olive oil{2%tsp}(for the crumb) into a small #bowl{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together, then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken breast{280%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until browned all over, ~{6-7%mins}.

> Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> Cook in batches if necessary - you want the chicken to brown, not stew.

Once browned, transfer the chicken to a medium bowl and set aside.

Return your (now empty) frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. When hot, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{4-5%mins}, stirring occasionally. Add the mushrooms and a little more oil if needed, then turn the heat up slightly. Fry until the mushrooms are browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%min} more.

Meanwhile, pop the carrots on the middle shelf of your oven to roast until tender, ~{18-25%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Stir the @water{100%ml}(for the sauce) and the @chicken stock paste{10%g} into the pan, then bring to the boil. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, bring back to the boil again, then turn down the heat. Simmer gently until reduced by a third, ~{3-4%mins}. Once the sauce has reduced, taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then return the chicken to the frying pan.

Transfer the chicken filling to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Layer on the cooked potato slices, then sprinkle over the breadcrumbs. Season with @pepper{} and bake on the top shelf of your oven until the top is golden brown, ~{10-12%mins}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Serve straight from the dish with the roasted carrots alongside. Enjoy!